definitions.definition: A family, Sturnidae , of passerine birds .

subdefinitions.definition: The common starling , Sturnus vulgaris , which has dark, iridescent plumage .

definitions.definition: An enclosure like a coffer-dam , formed of piles driven closely together, before any work or structure as a protection against the wash of the waves, commonly used to protects the piers of a bridge.
One of the piles used in forming such a breakwater .
A fish, rock trout ( Hexagrammos spp.), of the North Pacific, especially, Hexagrammos decagrammus , found in US waters.
